clonerepo clones git repositores into a pre-determined directory structure, and then cd-s into the cloned directory.

Usage:
  clonerepo [flags]

Flags:
  -o, --cd-to-output-dir   Outputs 'cd <cloned dir>' to stdout, which can be used for sourcing in a shell script. (default true)
      --config string      config file (default is: If $HOME/.config exists, it will be $HOME/.config/clonerepo/config.yaml. If not, it will be $HOME/.clonerepo.yaml)
  -d, --dry-run            Dry run, don't do any changes
  -h, --help               help for clonerepo
  -v, --verbose            Enables verbose output
